      <section id="tribute-info">
        <h2>A synopsis of Chris Cornell's life:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1964</strong> - Born Christopher John Boyle in Seattle, Washington, US</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1984</strong> - Soundgarden was formed</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1987</strong> - Released first EP, Screaming Life</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1988</strong> - Released debut album, Ultramega Ok</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1994</strong> - Soundgarden debuted at No. 1 on the Billboard 200 with Superunknown</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>1997</strong> - Soundgarden disbanded over creative differences</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>2010</strong> - Soundgarden reunited for several tours</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>2011</strong> - The band toured North America</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>2012</strong> - Final album, King Animal was released</li>
          <li id="timeline"><strong>2017</strong> - Death in Detroit, Michigan, US</li>
        <p id="tribute"><i> "He stepped to the microphone and sang the song and I couldn't believe it. It didn't just sound good. It didn't sound great. It sounded transcendent. And ... when there is an irreplaceable chemistry from the first moment, you can't deny it." - Tom Morello</i><p>
        <p id="link">Read more about Chris Cornell's prolific rock career <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Cornell">here</a>